    "description": "Wasm-GC subtype validation type confusion - recursive group validation compared struct fields before some SuperTypeVectors were initialized. In js/src/wasm/WasmTypeDef.h and WasmValidate.cpp, the fast subtype path could compare null/uninitialized STV pointers and conclude that incompatible wasm types were subtypes. Debug builds assert on superSTV; non-debug builds can validate modules with incompatible struct/array field types, allowing later generated code to treat values under the wrong wasm type. The fix forces a safe linear-search subtype path until the required supertype-vector state is initialized.",
